From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RHDL Local <rhdl@local>
Date: Mon, 23 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] printk: tolerate observed committed state in _prb_commit

On this platform bring-up we can observe cmpxchg returning failure while
the descriptor state is already updated to the requested committed value.
Treat that as success and keep WARN for all other mismatch states.
---
 kernel/printk/printk_ringbuffer.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/printk/printk_ringbuffer.c b/kernel/printk/printk_ringbuffer.c
index 6212612..fac352d 100644
--- a/kernel/printk/printk_ringbuffer.c
+++ b/kernel/printk/printk_ringbuffer.c
@@ -1776,8 +1776,11 @@ static void _prb_commit(struct prb_reserved_entry *e, unsigned long state_val)
 	 *    MB desc_reserve:D to desc_make_final:A
 	 */
 	if (!atomic_long_try_cmpxchg(&d->state_var, &prev_state_val,
-			DESC_SV(e->id, state_val))) { /* LMM(_prb_commit:B) */
-		WARN_ON_ONCE(1);
+			DESC_SV(e->id, state_val))) { /* LMM(_prb_commit:B) */
+		/* If observed state already equals requested committed value, continue. */
+		if (prev_state_val != DESC_SV(e->id, state_val)) {
+			WARN_ON_ONCE(1);
+		}
 	}
 
 	/* Restore interrupts, the reserve/commit window is finished. */
-- 
2.39.5

